---

OVERVIEW

RAT-win32 is a low-level Proof of Concept (PoC) demonstrating PE file
manipulation and process injection techniques on Windows x64.
The project is written in pure C++/WinAPI to maintain a minimal footprint
and avoid dependencies on high-level frameworks such as .NET.

---

COMPONENTS

  Injector.exe
    A CLI tool that appends a new section to an existing PE file and
    embeds raw source data (e.g. a DLL) directly into the target binary.

  LoadMe.exe
    A dropper that extracts the embedded payload from its own PE section,
    writes it to disk, establishes Registry persistence, executes the
    payload via rundll32.exe, and then self-deletes.

  ExampleDLL.dll
    The demonstration payload. Resolves its own path on disk, then
    injects itself into a target process (notepad.exe by default) using
    Manual Mapping and Process Hollowing.

---

TECHNICAL LOGIC

  1. INJECTION (Injector.exe)
     Calculates File/Section alignment and writes a new IMAGE_SECTION_HEADER
     into the target PE. Appends the raw payload bytes and updates
     NumberOfSections and SizeOfImage in the Optional Header.

  2. EXTRACTION (LoadMe.exe)
     Parses its own IMAGE_NT_HEADERS at runtime, locates the last section
     (PE32 and PE32+ are both supported), and returns a pointer to the
     embedded payload bytes.

  3. HOLLOWING + MANUAL MAP (ExampleDLL.dll / dllTools)
     Spawns the target process suspended. Reads PEB->ImageBaseAddress via
     NtQueryInformationProcess, then calls NtUnmapViewOfSection to clear
     the original image. Allocates a new region, writes PE headers and
     sections, patches the Relocation Table (IMAGE_REL_BASED_DIR64 only),
     and resolves the Import Address Table (IAT) entry by entry.

  4. EXECUTION
     Hijacks the suspended thread via GetThreadContext / SetThreadContext,
     pointing RIP to a shellcode stub that calls the DLL entry point with
     the correct x64 ABI arguments before jumping to it.

---

USAGE

  Step 1 - Build all three components from source (x64, MSVC or MinGW).

  Step 2 - Embed the payload DLL into the dropper:
             Injector.exe .extra LoadMe.exe ExampleDLL.dll

  Step 3 - Run the modified LoadMe.exe on the target system.

  For detailed per-component usage see the Docs/ directory.

