IMPORTANT NOTES

  Architecture   64-bit only. The relocation loop handles IMAGE_REL_BASED_DIR64
                 exclusively and the shellcode uses the x64 register ABI
                 (RCX, RDX, R8). Do not target 32-bit processes.

  Detection      Modern AV/EDR solutions may flag WriteProcessMemory,
                 SetThreadContext, NtUnmapViewOfSection, or the RWX
                 section characteristics set by Injector.

  Stealth        The manually mapped DLL does not appear in the PEB
                 InLoadOrderModuleList, so it is invisible to module
                 enumeration via standard API calls.

  Known issues   - The Registry value name written by LoadMe is a literal
                   format string instead of a meaningful identifier.
                   See docs/LoadMe/loadder.cpp.md for the fix.
                 - IAT patching resolves addresses from the injector's own
                   address space. See docs/ExampleDLL/dllTools.cpp.md for
                   the robust remote-base-adjusted approach.
                 - The export name "fristEntry" is a typo of "firstEntry".
                   Both LoadMe and ExampleDLL must be recompiled together
                   if you rename it.

